

# ğŸ¬ Movie Recommendation System - Content-Based Filtering

This project is a **Content-Based Movie Recommendation System** that recommends movies based on metadata such as genres, cast, director, tagline, and keywords. It uses **TF-IDF Vectorization** and **Cosine Similarity** to find similar movies based on user input.

---

## ğŸš€ Project Overview

Content-based recommender systems suggest similar items to a user based on a particular item. In this case, the system takes a movie title as input and recommends similar movies using the textual content of that movieâ€™s metadata.

---

## ğŸ§  Key Features

- ğŸ“„ Processes and cleans movie metadata
- ğŸ” Uses **TF-IDF (Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency)** to convert text to numerical features
- ğŸ“ Calculates **Cosine Similarity** between movies
- ğŸ” Recommends top 30 similar movies to the one entered by the user
- ğŸ§° Handles missing values and combines multiple features for better accuracy

---

## ğŸ“‚ Dataset Used

- **Name**: [TMDB 5000 Movie Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/tmdb/tmdb-movie-metadata)
- **Source**: Kaggle / The Movie Database (TMDB)
- **File**: `movies.csv`
- **Shape**: 4803 rows Ã— 24 columns

> Dataset contains metadata like genres, cast, director, keywords, overview, popularity, budget, etc.

